<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=103038722513112></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103038722513112><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103038722513112>RE: Mana</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103038722513112#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>197 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 26th 2:53 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't know if I'd say I do anything to &quot;waste mana&quot;, but based on 20 levels of play, have to agree that this is a fun class to play.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>As you can see by reading my signature, my main character Arjaizen is an upper-mid level wizard.  While I very much like playing him, it is pretty straightforward:  Most of the time, I debuff the mob's hot/cold resists with my Staff of Temperate Flux, sit until the mob's down a bubble of health, then hit it with a big nuke.  Hit it with another one when it reaches frenzy stage.  Sit and med, wait for next mob.  There are exceptions, but that's the routine 75% of the time.<br><br>With my enchanter, I'm mezzing adds, weakening and slowing mobs, speeding up and strengthening my tanks, breezing my casters, with the occasional dot or dd when needed.<br><br>I'm not a big fan of soloing my wizard, since he hasn't carried a melee weapon for a dozen levels.  Once his mana wears out, he is toast.  Period.  My enchanter?  So far, he can summon an animation, buff it up, and be ready to go it alone.  Lulls and mezzes mean he can single pull, and his nukes are good enough to help the animation bring the mob down.  No tiny daggers?  Charm a mob instead.<br><br>I've played a lot of different classes to the mid-20's, and thus far, I've found the enchanter to be the most varied and challenging.  Take that with a grain of salt though:  Once you get to the hig end game, a lot of things change, and i've not even begun to see how that affects the way different classes are played.<br><br>So far though, I've got to agree:  Enchanters are a blast. :-)<br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
