	   <tr><td colspan=2>Something I don't see much of is snare used with Charm.&nbsp;&nbsp;My gf plays a druid and I play an Enchanter.  Usually she pulls with Snare and brings two MOBs, both snared.  I'll Tash one while she drags the other around, and then Charm before it gets to me, then put it off on the other MOB.  They are both the same speed since both snared, and if Charm drops at an inopportune time the MOB is much easier to handle.  I can easily run ahead of it a bit and re-charm with no fear of it catching up to me.  I'll generally drop a choke line DOT on the MOB while the pet beats on it, depending on how well it is doing of course.  The object being to have the pet almost dead by the end of the fight.  After the charmed pet kills one mob, use /pet guard here to keep it nice and far away, walk off, break charm, she nukes once, maybe twice.  Exp for two MOBs and generally we use less than a bubble of mana each.  I've never seen the tactic posted anywhere, though I'm sure someone else has thought of it.  If your spouse hates casters and plays a ranger, you could easily have him Snare as you Charm and probably do two or three MOBs having the &quot;pet&quot; take most of the damage with the ranger just basically adding dmg output.  Hope this helps.<br><br>Morgann Brightmantle<br>47th Enchanter<br>Bristlebane<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
