	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with all those people that stated a Druid is the best partner. Besides the many important reasons such as SoW, heals, snare, track, ports, etc that was mentioned, I'll add in several other reasons too. <br><br>1) Druids are considered the 2nd best soloer in the game behind a necro. But a druid can kill more mobs and faster with quad kiting. With clarity, it gets insane as to what they can do.<br><br>2) A druid can also give the enchanter some needed hitpoint buffs such as PoTG. Regen buffs such as chloroplast to help you survive longer. Strenght buffs for those many times when you're encumbered after long successful battles. <br><br>3) Druids also get a summon bear pet at level 55. This gives you a nice alternate option of fighting if you like variety to keep things interest. The druid can also cast a damage shield on his/her and your pets along with the hitpoint, regen &amp; strenght buffs. You as the chanty add the haste and slow spells. Then all you have to do is say &quot;sick'em&quot; and watch the 2 pets attack the mobs.<br><br>An enchanter can be successful with also a shaman, ranger, wizzie, necro and I have no doubts about those classes. But I agree with the many people that suggested a druid. This is the best partner to have.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
