	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 17th 12:46 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is kind of an old post I know but I'm going to add my opinion that the ability to heal is not as important as it may seem for a partner, if you ask me.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>I have had tremendous success partnering with a necro friend of mine and more recently with a wizzy.  HPs are seldom the issue, it's the mana that runs out too fast.<br><br>You're a caster, you have several ways of keeping MOBs from getting close enough to beat on you.  Root, PB stuns, and a pet to name a few.<br><br>Add a wizard and you've got another rooter and a stunner.  Add a necro and you've got the ability to snare MOBs, and now either one of you can cast fear and kite the MOB.<br><br>So, if you ask me, add a caster.  There is no need for healing abilities.<br><br>I would go with either another caster type (two casters working well together can be extremely powerful) or maybe a melee.  If he goes with a melee I would then suggest something with the ability to heal himself.  A shadowknight, monk, ranger or a paladin.<br><br>If it were me, I'd make a mage, I've wanted to start one of those for a while now.<br><br>=)<br><br>Good luck.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
