	   <tr><td colspan=2>I did skip over the comment about not wanting to play a caster ... my bad.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>When partnering with my wizard buddy, I'll pull with tash (we usually hunt in areas with easy single pulls) and as I run the MOB back he hits him with Bonds, or else one of us roots.  I take my hit to engage pet, back off and cast a slow spell (IMO the slow line is almost crucial to soloing/partnering for me;  channeling roots or stuns while in melee range, saving pet HPs ... I LOVE slow), then with the wizard basically chain-nuking I will cast one or two nukes myself.  The MOBs go down quick this way, and it's pretty damn fun!<br><br>I love caster heavy groups, too.  They are harder to keep clean and organized.  Everyone needs to be on the ball and watch out for ill-gotten aggro.  But with the group you describe, with good timing I don't think the MOBs would have time to aggro anybody before they were splat!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
