	   <tr><td colspan=2>For my two cents, you would want a druid without question.<br><br>1) Healing.&nbsp;&nbsp;The hardest part of being an enchanter in early levels is sitting and waiting to heal.<br><br>2) Movement.  You will have sow relatively early, but more importantly, you will have snare from the beginning.  The ability to run away from mobs is priceless.  In future levels, the ports will make your life and enjoyment of the game much better.  With your mez and his snare, you will never need to die if you play smart.<br><br>Druid/chanter team is one of the strongest in the game.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
