	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10287400282327><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10287400282327>RE: Best Partner for Enchanter?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10287400282327#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>197 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 7th 1:18 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, since you are a DE enchanter, why doesn't he try a DE Shadow Knight?&nbsp;&nbsp;Still primarily a tanking class, but can also hurl about a few harmful spells that might mesh nicely with your debuffs. His pet and your animation together should provide a fair amount of additional offense to his melee attacks.  As a DE, he'll have very high INT, which is the mana stat for SKs.  Combine that with Breeze/Clarity, and he'll have what feels like an unlimited mana pool.<br><br>A Ranger would be good as well.  Decent AC, but terrific damage dealing once he gets to dual wield/double attack stage, and with some healing abilities that will only be enhanced by your Breeze/Clarity line.  And NEVER underestimate the usefulness of snare and tracking.<br><br>Then there's the Monk.  Outfit him with dual Polished Steel Ulaks to bump his HP by 50.  Since they're hand-to-hand weapons with good stats (phenomenal at that level actually,) He'll rip his way through to your level in a week, tops.  Faster with you PLing him.  Less flexibility than the Ranger and SK, but if you want to just pound on things, Monks can do that in spades.  <br><br>Finally, there's nothing wrong with another Warrior. If your spouse likes to RP, playing a different personality in a warrior will be as much fun as a different class.<br><br>As for &quot;best, 2nd, 3rd...&quot; i truly don't think there is such a thing.  A great player will take a mediocre character and make it great.  A lousy player will take a great character and STILL get his party killed.<br><br>That being said, personally, i find the Enchanter/SK pairing kind of intriguing.<br><br>Good luck...<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug  7 13:13:23 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
