	   <tr><td colspan=2>If I can give a serious answer to your post, which I know was meant to be partly funny (and was), on the one thing about no skill being required.<br><br>If you think no skill is required at all, after playing for a few months make a new character (a chanter would be nice for this exercise), and go back to your old haunts and group up with the new people there.&nbsp;&nbsp;You'll find, if you go back to Oasis or the orcs in EC, or Crushbone, that the groups you get into with newer players will quickly change your mind.  As they blithely break all your mezzes, refuse to pull breakaways off of you, and as the druids and clerics happily melee the five or six mobs the tanks pull at once, you will change your mind.<br><br>There is a HUGE fund of acquired knowledge on how to play the game in general, and group tactics in particular, that really has to be learned.  Playing EQ well requires more information, timing, and group dynamics than anything you do in school, right up through college.<br><br>My two cents.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
