	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 1st 8:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm making up to two blues of exp per kill with my level 13 Erudite enchanter fighting in Oasis. The way I solo here is pick out a nice croc or caiman, hit them with mez and start stacking tash and my debuffs, and choking to break the mez. My pet has a rusty weapon to increase his damage and is buffed up. I take a hit or two while I cast fear to get the mob running, and cast chaotic feedback as the croc takes off with my pet beating on him. I follow at a safe distance, renewing choke and fear as needed. Once the end is near I jump in and get a few hits on the mob to have a chance of a melee skill increase, perhaps to defense if my timing is off and he's not quite ready to run from low hit points.<br><br>If I'm full mana and near the zoneline I've taken out deepwater crocs using this method. It gets nerve wracking at times, and I've had to re-cast my pet under fire, but the way the exp bar jumps after the kill can't be beat. Bind yourself just across the zone in North Ro for a short CR if things go bad, and listen for high levels offering free buffs at the dock while they wait for the boat. It's not very mana efficient, but you'll have a blast taking out your first red with just your own wits and your pet. Good Hunting to you.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Sep&nbsp;&nbsp;1 08:41:57 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>There is good in everyone. Sometimes it just takes an autopsy to find it.....</td></tr>
