	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Warrens is very good, I agree.&nbsp;&nbsp; The exp and loot is hard to beat for the levels, and it's what you might call a &quot;target rich environment.&quot;<br><br>Around levels 12 to 16, you might go to Kerra Isle (AKA Kerra Ridge,) a nearby zone that's typically vacant, but has great exp (though the loot is weak,) especially for a solo Enchanter.<br><br>There's a pair of two-spawns that you can see almost immediately upon entering the zone, and once that spawn is broken, you and your pet can solo them forever.<br><br>One thing I like about this zone over the Warrens at that level is that you'll get good exp from everything in Kerra, while in the Warrens, you'll have to sift through tons of green kobolds to find the ones you want.  Also, Kerra Isle has a 20% exp bonus, which is always nice. &quot;Kill five, get one free!&quot;<br><br>The only down side I can see is that the loot (at least so far in my experience,) is pitiful.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Aug 13 16:20:37 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
