	   <tr><td colspan=2>Oasis is a good place to solo.<br><br>Try getting clarity while soloing. KEI is the best, but if not even breeze helps.<br><br>I would probably try to duo with a friend before soloing, but that is my preference.<br><br>For soloing, try summoning an Animation first. Then go cast Root and Choke on a target mob. While the mob is standing there taking damage, get some distance, sit and med.&nbsp;&nbsp;Try to Reroot and choke if you can so that you can med, but if not and your animation agros cast Stun and Fear. Recast fear as necessary and have a Nuke on hand to finish your mob off if you need to kill it fast(er).<br><br>The idea is to conserve/recover as much mana as you can while your mob is taking damage.<br><br>As for gear, a crude stein is nice.  Off hand, you could get a Stein of Moggok(+5 Dex +10 Int +25 vsDis +10 HP).  If you are looking for other cheap items, I would recommend going to the bazaar and doing a search for int/cha items for enchanters. Right click on the items and compare the items that are in your price range.<br><br>If you have a tradeskill around 220+(being an enchanter jewelry crafting will probably be your choice), you could try making a trophy.  They are *very* nice.  All of them have +10 Str, +10Int, +10Wis, +50 Cha (yes! +50) +5% skill bonus and clickable summon 100% WR no rent bag.  What's more they are Primary, Secondary or Range slot.  It is expensive in time and money to make, but I doubt there's a better range slot item to be had for your level or any level for that matter.  Check eqtraders.com for more info.<br><br>Best Regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>lvl 60 Phantasmist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
