	   <tr><td colspan=2>Go to OOT and solo Sirens (An Alluring Siren).<br>.<br>You'll find all the info on this site on the forum for Sirens under Antonica/Ocean of Tears/Bestiary<br>.<br>You have to get the tactic right, but you'll never see XP like it when you do. I went there today with my just-turned-11 chanter, and camped the spires on the way out from Freeport.&nbsp;&nbsp;6 hours later, I logged off my 14 chanter, and tomorrow I'll go and see the tougher and more numerous ones on the way out from Butcherblock.<br>.<br>At level 13 I gave up the advice on the forum about mezzing, tashing, and weakening before the fight starts.  It might make things easier when you pet is very weak at 11, but after it's much faster to simply pull with Choke, let it hit you once so pet takes over, then run to the other end of the rock you are standing on and cast one Chaotic Feedback.  Then med and let pet take over. With this tactic I did level 13 in 1.5 hours (faster than 11 or 12) without ever dropping below 80% mana. Lost no visible XP.<br>.<br>This tactic at 13 wasted no time - I sat and waited for each of the three spanws and they appeared just as I hit full mana every time. At 14 I would waste time on them I expect, which is why I am moving onto the larger/tougher group near BB. Anyway, I'll stop rambling here and simply recommend them for anyone looking for a place to send their 11-17 characters.<br>.<br>Verdan<br>(now with Chanter, Cleric, and Druid weaned on sirens)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Aug 30 16:00:16 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
