	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok here's how it works.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tash line reduces the NPC resistance to magic, we know that.  So it helps the initial casting of any spell take.  With duration spells (DOTs and Mezz and such) the NPC has the chance to resist the spell all over every tick or every time they get hit.  The die is rolled and checked against magic resist, charisma, level, etc. on each opportunity so if you were luck to get a duration spell to stick without tash it may not the second throw or third where with tash it has a much higher chance of not getting resisted. That means that there is a better chance of the Charm lasting the full duration, but it wont make it last longer than that.  Also your group casters are going to be more effective with their dots from your use of tash.  In general ....ALWAYS TASH ... the life you save may be your own ).<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Jul 26 13:01:38 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Yelwen Shapetwister<br>51th Season Enchanter<br>Dragonspawn of the Luclin Server<br><i>"What does not destroy us makes us stronger - what kills us makes us smarter"</i></td></tr>
