	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I would agree that tash is very useful, I don't feel the need to cast it on every mob, all the time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Case in point, if my group is comprised of high level characters (55+) and we are fighting blue mobs (hi 40's to low 50's), I generally don't worry about casting it.<br><br>Every Chanter has his or her own style of play to avoid agro while getting the job done, so you should explore various techinques and find what suits you.<br><br>Because melee doesn't effect root, I personally like to root, tash and/or debuff and med.  If root breaks and mobs go after me, often just standing up is enough to have the mobs forget me and go back to the tank.  If not, AE stun and reroot works too.<br><br>Best Regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>Lvl 60 Phantasmist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
