	   <a name=10287303661564></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10287303661564><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10287303661564>RE: Whirl till you Hurl</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=10287303661564#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=108438><span id=Sage>Aeldwan</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 7th 10:37 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Whirl and it's bigger counterpart Dyn's Dizzying Draught are useful in a PvP or Arena combat situation against a casting class. All stuns are. You can run DoT and nukes on the victim without a chance to break it save when the Nuke hits. In any other situation Root, Mez, or my favorite spells the Color stun line will do the job just as effectively and for less mana. Much faster casting time as well. If you are DoT rotting a Mob use Root not stun unless you are in VERY tight area where the Mob would still get to hit you if rooted. You will burn an amazing amount of mana on this though. In close up combat where you need to give the tanks a break from being beaten (often yourself as well), cast a Color Stun spell, then another shortly after (cycle the casting for Stun-Lock effect) which will do the job very well for the same mana and CANNOT be broken. You will get the full 4, 6 or 8 second duration. Bonus is you can lock more than one for AoE fun. Downside is more agro all around and it can penetrate through the floor or ceiling indoors. Hate safe spot is a good example. Mez cannot have DoT's running although you can remez after someone else nukes by timing the spell and using level 4 or 16 mez for cheapest cost. It is better to mez a target at distance, run up on it, debuff, taunt it off, THEN break it when it comes to distance attacks on casters and similar. Lastly, some mobs cannot be stunned but can be mezzed and rooted. Keep everything up for crowd control (especially 2 color stuns) and just have two slots for cycling buffs and similar. Because of all the other toys at your disposal, don't waste time on the whirl line unless you are going to play in the arena.<br> <br>Aeldwan the Enchanter<br>&nbsp;<br>Aeldwan the Enchanter<br>Wanderers of the Realm<br>Morell-Thule<br>"Doing the improbable daily to make the impossible look easy"</td></tr>
