	   <tr><td colspan=2>Against mobs that do not summon, I let mobs take about 10% damage before casting Tash. Then I cast Fetter and sit down.&nbsp;&nbsp;Against mobs that summon, I wait a moment or two before sitting.  If fetter breaks and the mob goes after me, I stand up.  Usually this is enough for the mob to refocus on the tank. If not, I PBAE Stun, recast Fetter while its stunned, step away and sit down. This tactic has worked just fine for me most of the time.<br><br>Although Horrifying Visage and Trix's Aug do work, they have slow refresh times so I don't use them unless the mobs are hitting really hard e.g.(200+).<br><br>I also frequently cast Bedlam and Rune V to soak some of the initial damage, if I find myself agroing a lot.<br><br>Best Regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>lvl 60 Phantasmist<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
