	   <tr><td colspan=2>My name is Farrnusno, and I play a 50 Enchanter on Karana.&nbsp;&nbsp;I almost exclusively play in full groups or raids, though from time to time (rarely) I have been known to duo with a soloing class.  I really am horrible at soloing, so rarely try unless I am camping something green for an item.<br><br>In group situations I tend to prefer multiple target &quot;chaotic&quot; aggro areas, as it tends to keep things exciting.  I am partial to dungeons, but not so much that I go out of my way to find one.<br><br>Generic Spell Line is as follows:<br><br>1) Current DD (rarely used, but good for wasting mana when you are full)<br><br>2) Highest Level Mezz<br><br>3) AOE Mezz (Rarely used, but when it is it usually saves me and my group)<br><br>4) Tash (Magic Resist Debuff, can there be anything better?)<br><br>5) Root (For getting rid of aggroed mobs until I can mezz, or do partial crowd control with unmezzables)<br><br>6) Haste<br><br>7) Clarity<br><br>8) Open slot for area specific spells, or spells that I feel like playing with when bored<br><br>6/7 I switch out for whatever buffs are needed, but those are the two I cast most often so I try to keep them up.<br><br>My chanter is my main character, and I have been playing him for a long time.  I also have a cleric alt as well.  As far as why I play an enchanter?  I would have to say that is because I enjoy being the focus of the group, knowing that I can mean the difference between a victory and a TPW.<br><br>-Farrnusno<br>Guild Leader<br>Souls of the Valiant<br>Karana Server<br>&nbsp;<br>Do not meddle in the affairs of giants, for you are crunchy and good with ketchup.<br><br>-Farrnusno<br>44 Enchanter<br>Guild Leader of Souls of the Valiant<br>Karana Server</td></tr>
