	   <tr><td colspan=2>This question has been answered many, many times on this board.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you scroll through the first few pages you're sure to find at least one post on this topic.<br><br>As far as not wanting to be DE for faction reasons, Enchanters get illusions and faction spells that allow us into almost any city with little or no actual faction-building.  You may want to go agnostic for this reason though, since illusions do not hide religions and that can get you killed.<br><br>Erudite's have the highest base INT and the second highest base CHA so they are an excellent choice.  Their starting zones kind of suck, though, and they have no natural night vision.<br><br>Ultimately, any race can excel at the enchanter class.  Play what you want to play.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
