	   <a name=102591306863541></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102591306863541><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102591306863541>RE: Tips</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102591306863541#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>180 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 5th 8:01 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.44]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Boy, that's kind of a broad subject but I'll do my best at addressing your question(s).<br><br>Best place to hunt ... probably NRO or Oasis, but different people will have different opinions on this.&nbsp;&nbsp;I also don't have SoL yet so I don't know of any zones up there that might be better.<br><br>If you are having troubles affording all your spells, get the ones that you absolutely need in order to fight (e.g. Tash, slow spells, nukes, pet spells) with first and fill in the blanks as you go.  If you just want to know which spells you'll never use and never want to buy, there's a lot that an enchanter get that hardly ever get used or never get used at all.  Still, I'd say get them all, especially at this level.  They're relatively cheap and you never know when one might come in handy.  Also, you can toy around with each one as you get it and figure out which 'lines' of spells you really use and which you never use.  Then, as you get higher you don't have to buy the useless ones.<br><br>Jewelcraft:  My advice is not to bother much at all until you get mid to high level.  Your intelligence will be higher affording you less failures and more rapid advancement.  You will also get intelligence buffs that will help in the same way.  It's expensive as well, so it's a good idea to wait until you have some spare 'bling bling' to spend.<br><br>One nice thing about the class that I have found is that the spells we use don't change a whole lot as we get higher in level.  I've had the same basic spell lineup for probably 20 levels or so.  The only thing that really changes is when I get a new level spell (like a new 'tash' or a new slow) that replaces the old one.<br><br>Feel free to ask any other (maybe more specific) questions you have.<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
