	   <tr><td colspan=2>My friend just turned 52 and I had a thought. (he's a chanter) We're trying to figure out if in a group with more than 2 mobs (say 3 are pulled) if he were to cast fascination then mez two of the mobs after a few seconds would this cause too much aggro or would it be better then just mez'n from the start?<br><br>Admittingly he doesn't see the need for it. I think it would be a neat strategy, then again I play a warrior.<br><br>Of course he'll end up doing what he is more comfortable with(which admittingly I would prefer seeing as that would keep a group alive)<br><br>Any thoughts on this would be of help. Or any strategies that he might find useful in the next couple of levels. <br><br>We're both just starting to hunt in a full group, so anything else you can add on that would be helpful. <br><br>We were just grabbing a healer before and getting great exp till around 49(for me, 51 for him) when we decided to head to KC and now we have seb keys too&lt;G&gt; <br><br>Thanks in advance. And I'm new to posting here so if this is a question that has been askedi n back posts or discussed im sorry, im just too lazy to check all 2000 posts&lt;g&gt;<br>&nbsp;<br>--------------------<br>Fiiz Thunderstrike<br>52 Warrior</td></tr>
